'''Bacax''' is a local god from the [[Ancient Rome|Roman]]-[[North Africa]]n region. Thought to have been a god of caves, Bacax is known from inscriptions at [[Cirta]] ([[Constantine, Algeria]]).

== References ==
*''Encyclopedia of Gods'', Michael Jordan, Kyle Cathie Limited, 2002

