{{Europe-myth-stub}}

'''Het Meerdal''' is a [[holiday village]] from [[Center Parcs]] in the [[Netherlands]]. It opened in 1971 in the town of [[America, Netherlands|America]] in the [[Limburg (Netherlands)|Limburg]] region.

Het Meerdal is the oldest village run by Center Parcs, although it was the third one to be built. The oldest two villages were sold, as they could not be expanded and brought into line with the other villages. These villages are now part of the [[Landal Greenparks]] operation.

