{{Infobox Union |name= MSzOSz |country= [[Hungary]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]], [[ETUC]], [[TUAC]] |members= 465,000 |full_name= National Confederation of Hungarian Trade Unions |native_name= Magyar Szakszervezetek Országos Szövetsége |image= [[File:MSZOSZ logo.png]] |founded= March, 1990 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Budapest]], Hungary |people= [[László Sandor]], president |website= [http://www.mszosz.hu/ www.mszosz.hu] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''National Confederation of Hungarian Trade Unions''' (MSzOSz) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Hungary]]. It was formed in 1990 and has a membership of 465,000 active members and 250,000 pensioners and apprentices.
The MSzOSz is affiliated with the [[International Trade Union Confederation]], and the [[European Trade Union Confederation]].
