{{Infobox language |name=Sawai |nativename=Weda |states=[[Indonesia]] |region=[[North Maluku]] province |speakers=12,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] (MP) |fam3=[[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear MP]] |fam4=[[Halmahera Sea languages|Halmahera Sea]] |fam5=[[South Halmahera languages|South Halmahera]] |fam6=[[Buli languages|Buli]] |dia1=Weda |dia2=Sawai |dia3=Kobe |dia4=Faya-Mafa |dia5=Messa-Dote |iso3=szw |glotto=sawa1247 |glottorefname=Sawai |notice=IPA }}
The '''Sawai language''' (also '''Weda''') is a [[South Halmahera languages|South Halmahera language]] of [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] stock spoken in Weda and Gane Timor districts of southern [[Halmahera]], northern [[North Maluku|Maluku Province]], [[Indonesia]]. There are approximately 12,000 speakers.
==Sounds== Below is description of the Kobe dialect of Sawai spoken in the villages of [[Lelilef Woyebulan]] and [[Kobe Peplis]].
===Consonants=== Sawai has 14 [[consonant]]s:
{| class="wikitable IPA" |- style="font-size: 80%;" | colspan="2" | &nbsp; ! [[labial consonant|Labial]] ! [[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ! [[Palatal]] ! [[Velar consonant|Velar]] |- ! style="font-size: 80%; text-align: left;" colspan="2" | [[Stop consonant|Stop]] | p&nbsp;&nbsp;b | t&nbsp;&nbsp;d | &nbsp; | k&nbsp;&nbsp;ɡ |- ! style="font-size: 80%; text-align: left;" colspan="2" | [[Fricative]] | f | s | &nbsp; | &nbsp; |- ! style="font-size: 80%; text-align: left;" colspan="2" | [[Nasal stop|Nasal]] | m | n | &nbsp; | ŋ |- ! style="font-size: 80%; text-align: left;" rowspan="2" | [[Approximant]] | style="font-size: x-small; text-align: left;" | [[central consonant|central]] | w | &nbsp; | j | &nbsp; |- | style="font-size: x-small; text-align: left;" | [[lateral consonant|lateral]] | &nbsp; | l | &nbsp; | &nbsp; |}
===Vowels=== Sawai has 7 [[vowel]]s:
