{{no footnotes|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox company | name = TV Vlaanderen | logo = TV Vlaanderen Digitaal logo.svg | logo_size = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | slogan = | foundation = 2006 | location = [[Zaventem]], [[Belgium]] | key_people = K. Pauwels, General Director | industry = [[Pay TV]] | products = [[DVB-S2]], [[DVB-T2]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = [[M7 Group]] | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|https://www.tv-vlaanderen.be/}} | footnotes = }} [[File:TV-Vlaanderen.jpg|thumb|TV Vlaanderen Digitaal previous logo]] '''TV Vlaanderen''' is a [[Digital data|digital]] [[satellite television]] and [[terrestrial television]] service provider for the [[Flanders]] region in [[Belgium]].
TV Vlaanderen's customers are mostly people living in [[Flanders]]. However, as TV Vlaanderen is officially available to the whole of Belgium, TV Vlaanderen also has many Flemish customers living in the French-speaking part of Belgium due to the unavailability of Dutch-language TV channels on [[Cable Television]] platform's in [[Wallonia]].
Like the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] satellite television provider [[CanalDigitaal]], TV Vlaanderen is owned by M7 Group S.A..
== History == Originally, TV Vlaanderen only offered a [[DVB-S2]] satellite television service, using the [[SES Astra]] satellites at [[Astra 19.2°E]] and at [[Astra 23.5°E]].
In 2017, it started a [[DVB-T2]] terrestrial service branded "Antenne TV", which uses the [[Norkring]] transmitter network.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20171207_03230016 |title=TV Vlaanderen lanceert nieuw aanbod: 15 zenders voor 9,95 euro |date=7 December 2017 |publisher=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |language=Dutch |trans-title=TV Vlaanderen launches new offer: 15 channels for 9.95 euro }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.totaaltv.nl/nieuws/m7-gaat-in-belgie-op-dvbt2-uitzenden-met-tv-vlaanderen/ |title=M7 gaat in België op DVB-T2 uitzenden met TV Vlaanderen |author=Jan-Hein Visser |date=13 November 2017 |publisher=Totaal TV |language=Dutch |trans-title=M7 to start broadcasting DVB-T2 in Belgium with TV Vlaanderen }}</ref>
== Smart card == The Flemish public and commercial broadcasts are not freely available via satellite. To receive the Flemish broadcasts, a [[Smartcard]] is required to decipher the [[Mediaguard]] signal.
A standard [[DVB-S2]] receiver is used, which can also receive [[free-to-air]] broadcasts.
