{{Infobox military structure |name = West Battery |native_name = |partof = [[Fortifications of Gibraltar]] |location =[[Gibraltar]] |image = |caption = |map_type = Gibraltar |map_size = 300 |map_alt = |map_caption = Location in [[Gibraltar]] |type = [[Artillery battery]] |coordinates = {{coord|36.1136|-5.347|type:landmark_region:GI|display=inline}} |code = |built = |builder = |materials = |height = |used = |demolished = |condition = |ownership = [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]] |open_to_public = |controlledby = |garrison = |current_commander = |commanders = |occupants = |battles = |events = |image2 = |caption2 = }} '''West Battery''' is an [[artillery battery]] in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. It is situated on the escarpment of [[Windmill Hill, Gibraltar|Windmill Hill]] in the south of the territory.
The battery stands on the site of two emplacements originally constructed under General [[Edward Cornwallis]] between 1762–77. It takes its name from its position facing south-west. In the late 19th century it became (along with [[Buffadero Battery]] and [[Jews' Cemetery Battery]]) one of three batteries on or below Windmill Hill to be equipped with [[BL 9.2 inch gun Mk I–VII|BL 9.2 inch gun Mk V]] guns, two of which were installed in 1886. These were upgraded to [[BL 9.2 inch gun Mk IX–X|BL 9.2 inch gun Mk X]] guns in 1901, mounted on Mark V [[barbette]]s. They faced out towards the Mediterranean to cover naval traffic through the [[Straits of Gibraltar]].<ref name="Hughes378" />
The 9.2-inch guns remained in service until 1950. They were subsequently replaced by three 5.25-inch dual-purpose guns for coastal and anti-aircraft defence. Although the guns have since been removed, the emplacements and the structure of the battery are still clearly visible.<ref name="Hughes378">{{cite book|title=Strong as the Rock of Gibraltar|last1=Hughes|first1=Quentin|last2=Migos|first2=Athanassios|publisher=Exchange Publications|year=1995|page=378}}</ref>
